Subject: [announce] Ccpathnames revision 0.1d0

			      CCPathnames
			      ===========


This package installs a C11 language library implementing Unix pathnames
manipulation functions.

  This package  supports POSIX platforms.   This package depends  on the
package CCExceptions, at least version 0.6.4-devel.3.

  The package  makes use  of the  GNU Autotools  and it  is tested  on a
GNU+Linux system.  It is distributed under the GNU Lesser General Public
License version 3.0 or, at your option, any later version.

  The latest release of this package can be downloaded from:

	<https://bitbucket.org/marcomaggi/ccpathnames/downloads>

development takes place at:

	      <https://github.com/marcomaggi/ccpathnames/>

and as backup at:

	    <https://bitbucket.org/marcomaggi/ccpathnames/>

the documentation is available online:

	  <https://marcomaggi.github.io/docs/ccpathnames.html>

the package CCExceptions is available at:

	     <https://github.com/marcomaggi/ccexceptions/>


Notes for revision 0.1d0
------------------------

* First revision.


